WEBVTT

00:01.653 --> 00:03.220
- Previously on "You"...

00:03.264 --> 00:04.265
- Everyone just
calls me Beck.

00:04.308 --> 00:05.918
And you are Joe?

00:05.962 --> 00:07.137
- Goldberg.

00:07.181 --> 00:09.270
A guy needs to
protect himself,

00:09.313 --> 00:11.663
and your name was
a glorious place to start.

00:11.707 --> 00:14.014
The next thing our little
friend the Internet gave me

00:14.057 --> 00:15.102
was your address.

00:15.145 --> 00:17.060
[dramatic music]

00:17.104 --> 00:18.627
- Professor Leahy.

00:18.670 --> 00:20.585
- Professor Obvious
wants to sleep with you.

00:20.629 --> 00:22.413
Your friends
are disloyal,

00:22.457 --> 00:24.372
and that Peach is
the queen bee.

00:24.415 --> 00:27.114
- How broke are you?

00:27.157 --> 00:30.160
- Benjamin J. Ashby, Greenwich
born, boarding school bred.

00:30.204 --> 00:32.771
- God, you
make me insane.

00:32.815 --> 00:34.556
♪

00:34.599 --> 00:36.166
- Oh!

00:36.210 --> 00:38.081
♪

00:38.125 --> 00:39.300
I think I know you.

00:39.343 --> 00:41.867
- Oh, right.
Of course.

00:41.911 --> 00:45.262
You're smart, except in
the ways you are really not,

00:45.306 --> 00:47.308
like not locking
your phone.

00:47.351 --> 00:48.874
Maybe we could get
a drink sometime.

00:48.918 --> 00:50.441
- Sure.

00:50.485 --> 00:52.139
- What you really need is
someone to save you.

00:52.182 --> 00:54.141
- Man,
I'm thinking maybe--

00:54.184 --> 00:56.230
Whatever you think
I did...

00:56.273 --> 00:57.231
- I can help, Beck.

00:57.274 --> 00:58.406
- ...you got
the wrong guy.

00:58.449 --> 01:01.409
- Let me help you.

01:01.452 --> 01:02.888
- ♪ Well, I went...

01:02.932 --> 01:05.239
- Tonight's the night,
Beck.

01:05.282 --> 01:07.154
Our first date.

01:07.197 --> 01:10.809
It just feels right,
right?

01:10.853 --> 01:14.987
- ♪ I stood
and watched her fall ♪

01:15.031 --> 01:17.468
- I'm looking forward to it,
and I think,

01:17.512 --> 01:19.644
obvious hangover aside,
you are, too.

01:19.688 --> 01:22.299
But I've read people wrong
in the past.

01:22.343 --> 01:25.476
One day, I'll tell you
about Candace,

01:25.520 --> 01:28.131
every red flag
I was blind to,

01:28.175 --> 01:30.177
how destroyed I was.

01:30.220 --> 01:32.092
What can I say?
We all have baggage.

01:32.135 --> 01:35.312
But I feel like I'm dealing
with it the right way.

01:35.356 --> 01:37.793
Not bothering you,
just checking it.

01:37.836 --> 01:41.362
- ♪ For they know
the great imposter ♪

01:41.405 --> 01:43.146
♪

01:43.190 --> 01:45.409
- Hanging with you like this is
admittedly honing skills

01:45.453 --> 01:50.240
I never knew I'd need,
but hey, handy.

01:50.284 --> 01:54.636
- ♪ And he's playing a part

01:54.679 --> 01:56.681
- You can't afford new clothes,
but let's be real.

01:56.725 --> 01:59.206
You'd look perfect
in a potato sack.

01:59.249 --> 02:02.339
- ♪ Oh, can't she see

02:02.383 --> 02:05.168
- Not a criticism,
God knows I am, too,

02:05.212 --> 02:06.561
but you seem distracted.

02:06.604 --> 02:09.520
- ♪ Soon she'll
learn her fate ♪

02:09.564 --> 02:12.044
- Of course,
a new phone.

02:12.088 --> 02:14.221
Not sure how you went
24 hours without one.

02:14.264 --> 02:17.180
As you activate
your new friend there,

02:17.224 --> 02:20.314
I know you think you're also
deactivating your old one.

02:20.357 --> 02:22.054
But here's where
you're wrong.

02:22.098 --> 02:23.578
Your old phone,
which I have,

02:23.621 --> 02:26.102
is still logged
into the cloud.

02:26.146 --> 02:29.801
♪

02:29.845 --> 02:33.501
And that means
I'm still logged into you.

02:33.544 --> 02:35.720
Sci-fi movies
are so wrong.

02:35.764 --> 02:37.592
Technology is our friend.

02:37.635 --> 02:39.768
- You've reached Benji.
Leave some love. Namaste.

02:39.811 --> 02:41.552
- Hey, look,
you haven't texted back.

02:41.596 --> 02:44.468
Just let me know
you're okay, okay?

02:44.512 --> 02:48.211
That's all I ask.
This is really annoying, Benji.

02:48.255 --> 02:51.867
[somber music]

02:51.910 --> 02:53.869
- It is annoying.

02:53.912 --> 02:56.219
You're not thinking about us,
you're thinking about him.

02:56.263 --> 02:59.570
I kind of thought I took care
of that for you, Beck.

02:59.614 --> 03:01.659
- Want to start off the class
this morning?

03:01.703 --> 03:03.270
- Sure.
- Good.

03:03.313 --> 03:04.880
My last T.A. was like
a little mouse,

03:04.923 --> 03:06.273
afraid of public speaking.
- Oh, that's my job.

03:06.316 --> 03:08.013
- Well, lucky us,
you're good at it.

03:08.057 --> 03:10.102
We're still on for tomorrow,
drinks, poetry?

03:10.146 --> 03:12.235
- Nothing if not up
for both of those.

03:12.279 --> 03:15.238
[dramatic music]

03:15.282 --> 03:20.287
♪

03:20.330 --> 03:21.853
[bells jingle]

03:21.897 --> 03:23.942
- Hey, they came
for the big day.

03:23.986 --> 03:25.770
Want me move them down
to the basement?

03:25.814 --> 03:27.685
- No, I'll do that. Just get
started on the window display.

03:27.729 --> 03:30.688
- Oh, hey, I was thinking about
making cookies for #ReleaseDay.

03:30.732 --> 03:33.256
Amanda Chantal Bacon has a dope
recipe in "Moon Juice Cookbook:

03:33.300 --> 03:35.432
Cook Cosmically for Body,
Beauty, and Consciousness."

03:35.476 --> 03:36.868
- Kill me.

03:36.912 --> 03:37.782
Sounds great, Ethan.

03:37.826 --> 03:39.393
- Oh, and that kid
is back.

03:39.436 --> 03:42.004
- Paco?

03:46.269 --> 03:48.140
Hey, speed reader.

03:48.184 --> 03:49.229
- Hi, Joe.

03:49.272 --> 03:50.752
- What are you reading?

03:50.795 --> 03:52.319
- This book about werewolves
the girls in my class

03:52.362 --> 03:53.711
won't stop talking about.

03:53.755 --> 03:58.107
It's more about love stuff
than werewolf stuff.

03:58.150 --> 04:00.457
- There should be
right up here...

04:00.501 --> 04:03.852
Yeah, it's right here.
Here, try this.

04:06.071 --> 04:07.421
- "Frankenstein"?

04:07.464 --> 04:09.814
- Yeah, the monster is
really cool and scary

04:09.858 --> 04:12.469
but also not really
the monster.

04:12.513 --> 04:14.471
- What does that mean?

04:14.515 --> 04:15.864
- Just read it.
You can tell me.

04:15.907 --> 04:19.215
Ethan's got snacks.
Set 'em up.

04:37.059 --> 04:40.149
- Let me the hell
outta here!

04:40.192 --> 04:41.498
Now!

04:41.542 --> 04:43.239
- Settle down, Benji.

04:43.283 --> 04:44.284
Let's talk.

04:44.327 --> 04:47.287
[dramatic music]

04:47.330 --> 04:48.375
♪

04:52.248 --> 04:54.468
Okay, granted I didn't think
too far ahead

04:54.511 --> 04:56.165
when I swung
that mallet.

04:56.208 --> 04:59.037
I just knew Benji was
the worst kind of poison,

04:59.081 --> 05:01.301
the kind you know is bad
but can't stop taking.

05:01.344 --> 05:03.694
So I did what I had to do
to help you, Beck.

05:03.738 --> 05:06.306
And now, there's
an adult human male

05:06.349 --> 05:07.568
in the basement
of this bookstore.

05:07.611 --> 05:08.917
- Somebody!

05:08.960 --> 05:10.179
- The basement's
soundproof.

05:10.222 --> 05:11.528
- Aah!

05:11.572 --> 05:13.443
- The owner loved to
read in peace down here.

05:13.487 --> 05:15.358
I'm sorry.

05:15.402 --> 05:16.838
- I told you,
I don't know who you are,

05:16.881 --> 05:19.362
I don't know why I'm here.
I swear.

05:19.406 --> 05:22.147
- Confession, I have no idea
what to do with him now.

05:22.191 --> 05:24.367
- I'm gonna give you
my family lawyer's number.

05:24.411 --> 05:25.760
He'll get you paid.

05:25.803 --> 05:27.544
- Of course he thinks
I want money.

05:27.588 --> 05:29.198
- You know
who my father is?

05:29.241 --> 05:32.201
- Benjamin Ashby II,
hedge fund manager.

05:32.244 --> 05:34.377
- We have a jet. We'll send
you anywhere in the world.

05:34.421 --> 05:38.120
- Best case, that's somewhere
far away from you, Beck.

05:38.163 --> 05:41.558
Worst case,
that ends with prison time.

05:41.602 --> 05:44.256
Not an option.

05:46.128 --> 05:48.609
- It's a poppy seed bagel,
extra schmear.

05:48.652 --> 05:51.394
- Go to hell.

05:51.438 --> 05:53.570
I don't eat gluten.

05:53.614 --> 05:56.268
It's an allergy, okay?
That shit is real.

05:56.312 --> 05:59.271
Gluten, dairy, if I ate
a peanut, I could die.

05:59.315 --> 06:02.187
- Well, gosh,
whatever can I get you?

06:02.231 --> 06:05.147
- I'd just like a bare burger
wrapped in chard.

06:05.190 --> 06:06.844
Or I could do sushi.

06:06.888 --> 06:08.063
- Sushi?

06:08.106 --> 06:11.371
- My diet is limited.
Please?

06:12.633 --> 06:14.983
Whoever you are,
you're not a killer.

06:15.026 --> 06:16.550
- Oh, how I wish I was.

06:16.593 --> 06:18.682
This would be
much less complicated.

06:18.726 --> 06:20.771
- Let me out of here.

06:20.815 --> 06:24.035
I won't say anything
to anyone.

06:24.079 --> 06:26.560
- He doesn't even know my name.
I can figure this out.

06:26.603 --> 06:28.605
- I'm claustrophobic.

06:28.649 --> 06:31.652
My blood sugar's low.

06:31.695 --> 06:34.655
[dramatic music]

06:34.698 --> 06:36.396
- Is this sugar?

06:36.439 --> 06:39.399
I found it in your wallet along
with three bars of Xanax,

06:39.442 --> 06:42.053
Adderall, half a sheet of,
I think, acid, is it?

06:42.097 --> 06:43.533
- Whatever.
It's not even for me.

06:43.577 --> 06:44.665
I network.
I own a business.

06:44.708 --> 06:46.275
- That's right,
Home Soda.

06:46.318 --> 06:48.538
- It's artisanal.
It's gonna blow up.

06:48.582 --> 06:49.626
- Is it?

06:49.670 --> 06:52.281
Do your investors know
you do heroin?

06:52.324 --> 06:55.545
Or your--your father?
How about your girlfriend?

06:55.589 --> 06:58.635
- I don't have
a girlfriend.

07:01.377 --> 07:03.510
Oh, shit!

07:03.553 --> 07:06.382
That's where
I know you from.

07:09.254 --> 07:10.517
You were in the cab!

07:10.560 --> 07:12.040
Beck's cab!

07:12.083 --> 07:13.563
She--she said
your name.

07:13.607 --> 07:15.609
It's Jimmy. No.

07:15.652 --> 07:18.612
- This is Joe.
He literally saved my life.

07:18.655 --> 07:19.830
- It's Joe!

07:19.874 --> 07:22.442
- Now,
that's a complication.

07:22.485 --> 07:25.488
- Do not tell me that you're
doing this because of Beck.

07:25.532 --> 07:26.576
She's not my girlfriend.

07:26.620 --> 07:28.099
You can have her!

07:28.143 --> 07:29.274
Take her!

07:29.318 --> 07:30.493
- Careful, Benji.

07:30.537 --> 07:32.147
Not winning
any points.

07:32.190 --> 07:33.191
- If you knew her,

07:33.235 --> 07:35.585
you would not be
putting me in a cage

07:35.629 --> 07:39.546
and ruining your life over
Guinevere Goddamn Beck!

07:39.589 --> 07:42.505
[dramatic music]

07:42.549 --> 07:43.550
- If you want out,

07:43.593 --> 07:45.508
you'll do what I want.

07:45.552 --> 07:51.514
♪

07:51.558 --> 07:53.429
- The days of being with a man
who doesn't value you,

07:53.473 --> 07:54.865
those are over.

07:54.909 --> 07:57.520
If we can get over
the first date hump.

07:57.564 --> 07:59.087
[cell phone buzzes]

07:59.130 --> 08:01.655
- Can't help it,
worried about Benji.

08:01.698 --> 08:03.352
- That's why it's so crucial
Benji's out of your picture.

08:03.395 --> 08:05.223
- Please, he's off
getting shit-faced.

08:05.267 --> 08:07.182
- Or he's in
some kind of trouble.

08:07.225 --> 08:09.576
- What we have right now is
just a little spark.

08:09.619 --> 08:11.708
Every choice is
a message.

08:11.752 --> 08:14.494
With Candace, I always felt
like I was pushing.

08:15.886 --> 08:18.628
But now I realize,
can't force it,

08:18.672 --> 08:20.587
the timing, the spark.
[cell phone buzzes]

08:20.630 --> 08:23.241
So you tell me if
you're too distracted, Beck.

08:23.285 --> 08:25.853
You decide.

08:25.896 --> 08:28.899
- Sure. Looking forward.
Free at six.

08:28.943 --> 08:31.946
- ♪ Give me a purpose

08:31.989 --> 08:34.339
♪ Something I can be

08:34.383 --> 08:37.604
♪

08:37.647 --> 08:40.650
♪ Give me a purpose

08:40.694 --> 08:44.001
♪ Something I can see

08:44.045 --> 08:45.960
♪ Whoa ho, ho

08:46.003 --> 08:48.571
- So it was just one of those
cheesy diaries with a lock,

08:48.615 --> 08:50.399
but I couldn't
stop writing.

08:50.442 --> 08:54.055
I just--I felt better having it
all down on paper, you know?

08:54.098 --> 08:56.274
And then I did this little
creative writing assignment

08:56.318 --> 08:58.146
and it just blew
my teacher's mind.

08:58.189 --> 09:00.757
She acted like it was the best
thing she'd...[voice fades]

09:00.801 --> 09:03.325
- Honestly, part of me thought
this date would never come,

09:03.368 --> 09:05.936
and now it feels so easy,
so right.

09:05.980 --> 09:09.592
This is how our story goes,
Beck.

09:09.636 --> 09:11.725
- And here I am.

09:11.768 --> 09:15.511
Sometimes you just,
you do things on instinct

09:15.555 --> 09:18.906
because you have to, and
then you scramble, you know.

09:18.949 --> 09:22.779
- Yeah, I kinda know.

09:22.823 --> 09:25.129
- I totally didn't Google
you, but if I did,

09:25.173 --> 09:27.741
I might discover you
aren't on social media.

09:27.784 --> 09:31.571
- Fact, it renders you insanely
vulnerable with zero upside.

09:31.614 --> 09:32.963
I'm an old-fashioned guy.

09:33.007 --> 09:34.965
I like real life.

09:35.009 --> 09:36.576
- What about your job?

09:36.619 --> 09:37.751
- Bookstore manager or--

09:37.794 --> 09:39.927
or international
super spy, which is--

09:39.970 --> 09:42.930
- I mean,
is that your goal or--

09:44.801 --> 09:46.498
- I know I'm in a city
full of people

09:46.542 --> 09:49.240
with--with--with big, fat
neon sign aspirations.

09:49.284 --> 09:53.157
And I know it's not cool to say
and it's not big and flashy...

09:55.986 --> 09:58.728
but I love books,

09:58.772 --> 10:03.472
and I want my life to be about
what I actually love.

10:03.515 --> 10:06.301
- Yeah, I get that.

10:07.519 --> 10:09.609
[cell phone rings]

10:11.567 --> 10:14.309
Sorry, just a second,
okay?

10:14.352 --> 10:16.659
- Yeah, go ahead.

10:16.703 --> 10:19.793
- Hey.

10:19.836 --> 10:22.796
Yeah, I know it's serious,
Peach.

10:22.839 --> 10:24.058
I'm the one who told you
I was worried.

10:24.101 --> 10:27.409
Okay.
Yes, I'm coming.

10:30.717 --> 10:33.545
I'm sorry,
I have to go.

10:33.589 --> 10:36.636
This friend, he just--apparently
he had to go meet someone

10:36.679 --> 10:38.246
and never came back.

10:38.289 --> 10:39.639
It's worrying.

10:39.682 --> 10:40.988
- We can pick it up some other
time if you have to.

10:41.031 --> 10:43.251
- All right, thank you.

10:43.294 --> 10:45.209
- I hope your friend
is okay.

10:45.253 --> 10:46.776
I thought
I'd done it,

10:46.820 --> 10:48.952
gotten Benji
out of our way.

10:48.996 --> 10:51.215
Looks like I have to
finish the job.

10:55.655 --> 10:57.395
- To figure out what to do
with the poster boy

10:57.439 --> 10:59.267
for white male privilege
in the cage,

10:59.310 --> 11:01.617
I need to understand
who he truly is.

11:01.661 --> 11:04.751
And to do that, I need to know
what he cares about.

11:04.794 --> 11:06.361
- This is totally unfair.

11:06.404 --> 11:07.710
If I knew you were
gonna quiz me,

11:07.754 --> 11:09.669
I'd have put more recent
books on the list.

11:09.712 --> 11:12.019
- So bottom line, you've never
even read "On the Road."

11:12.062 --> 11:13.803
- It's very possible to
read a book

11:13.847 --> 11:16.719
without having to read it
in the traditional manner.

11:16.763 --> 11:17.851
You can read
about a book.

11:17.894 --> 11:21.855
- Yeah, I get it.

11:21.898 --> 11:23.160
You're a fraud.

11:23.204 --> 11:25.075
- Here, give me
the stupid book.

11:25.119 --> 11:27.208
I'll read it right now,
you sadistic prick.

11:27.251 --> 11:30.385
Anything to
get me out of here.

11:30.428 --> 11:32.604
- I do understand something
about you now, Beck.

11:32.648 --> 11:35.999
You somehow think this guy
is all you deserve.

11:36.043 --> 11:37.914
You're looking a little gray
and mealy in there.

11:37.958 --> 11:40.177
- Yeah, no shit.
You stole my stash!

11:40.221 --> 11:42.876
- I thought it
wasn't for you.

11:42.919 --> 11:44.834
- Fine.

11:44.878 --> 11:48.142
You happy? It's mine.
I'm a chipper.

11:48.185 --> 11:51.319
I never do it more than
three days in a row.

11:51.362 --> 11:52.755
And I'm quitting.

11:52.799 --> 11:56.019
- Okay, only if
you're quitting.

11:59.806 --> 12:03.113
- [sighs]

12:04.985 --> 12:07.117
- Doesn't work
that way.

12:07.161 --> 12:10.468
It's only one way.

12:12.209 --> 12:14.951
- Thank you.
Thank you.

12:18.825 --> 12:21.915
- Just one more thing.

12:23.786 --> 12:24.744
Password.

12:24.787 --> 12:27.790
- [scoffs and laughs]

12:32.839 --> 12:34.710
Leanna.

12:34.754 --> 12:36.407
L-E-A-N-N-A.

12:36.451 --> 12:39.715
- His phone lock is
another girl's name, Beck.

12:39.759 --> 12:42.544
Jesus Christ.

12:42.587 --> 12:44.415
[dramatic music]

12:44.459 --> 12:45.634
- Oh, yeah.

12:45.677 --> 12:52.380
♪

12:52.423 --> 12:54.991
- Well, he's been living
a frankly off-brand life

12:55.035 --> 12:56.906
for a guy who markets
health soda.

12:56.950 --> 12:58.865
Based on the evidence,

12:58.908 --> 13:00.214
he's not missing you
when you're gone.

13:00.257 --> 13:02.782
You don't mean anything
to him.

13:02.825 --> 13:08.875
♪

13:11.703 --> 13:13.140
Say cheese.

13:13.183 --> 13:14.837
- I was worried.
I called his mother.

13:14.881 --> 13:16.273
We were about to call
the police, and he's high

13:16.317 --> 13:18.014
in some random shitburg
in Massachusetts

13:18.058 --> 13:19.929
according to
his geolocation.

13:19.973 --> 13:22.671
- Don't say geolocation.
You're not a stalker.

13:22.714 --> 13:24.804
- At least we know he's fine,
just being the worst.

13:24.847 --> 13:28.329
- So we're all gonna go try
that new bar tonight, right?

13:28.372 --> 13:29.243
In SoHo.

13:29.286 --> 13:31.071
- You are such a lush.

13:31.114 --> 13:32.986
- Shit, I can't go.
I'm sorry.

13:33.029 --> 13:35.989
I'm supposed to have drinks
with my thesis adviser.

13:36.032 --> 13:37.251
- Oh.

13:37.294 --> 13:39.906
- Ugh, scale of one
to ten, how pervy?

13:39.949 --> 13:41.777
- He won an award
for a book of poems

13:41.821 --> 13:45.172
that probably has 35 references
to, like, vagina lips.

13:45.215 --> 13:47.261
- Well, banging your professor
is like a grad school

13:47.304 --> 13:48.828
rite of passage.
- Is it?

13:48.871 --> 13:50.699
- Annika's like the Wikipedia
page for slut, so...

13:50.742 --> 13:52.919
- Whatever. I banged
my bio professor.

