of all places

29:23.805 --> 29:27.548
at the very right moment.

29:30.116 --> 29:32.727
Oh, it's time
for the toast.

29:32.771 --> 29:35.730
[Anoraak's "Figure"]

29:35.774 --> 29:40.866
♪

29:40.909 --> 29:44.565
- ♪ Nothing to fear about me,
darling ♪

29:44.608 --> 29:46.523
♪

29:46.567 --> 29:48.221
- So in the time
I was in there,

29:48.264 --> 29:51.006
you attract Benji 2.0.

29:51.050 --> 29:52.921
Peach looks thrilled.

29:52.965 --> 29:54.705
Are you thrilled?

29:54.749 --> 29:57.056
What do you want?

29:57.099 --> 30:01.060
♪

30:01.103 --> 30:03.627
- ♪ We'll figure it out

30:03.671 --> 30:07.066
♪

30:07.109 --> 30:09.285
- So which Beck are you?

30:09.329 --> 30:12.506
The one I see
or the one Benji does?

30:12.549 --> 30:17.859
♪

30:17.903 --> 30:19.818
- Hey, stranger.

30:19.861 --> 30:21.994
How are you holding up?

30:22.037 --> 30:24.083
Having fun?

30:26.128 --> 30:28.304
- [sighs]

30:28.348 --> 30:31.438
Beck.

30:32.613 --> 30:36.138
Why did you
bring me here?

30:36.182 --> 30:39.489
- I don't know.
I thought it could be fun?

30:39.533 --> 30:41.970
- I don't think I have
a lot in common

30:42.014 --> 30:45.060
with your
other friends.

30:45.104 --> 30:47.584
- I like that about you.

30:50.065 --> 30:51.980
I always think I'm
gonna love these things,

30:52.024 --> 30:54.069
yet somehow never do.

30:54.113 --> 30:55.897
- Then why
did we come?

30:55.941 --> 30:59.074
- It's been this way
since Brown.

30:59.118 --> 31:01.598
Just feels like
I'm getting sucked in

31:01.642 --> 31:03.774
and I could just be me,

31:03.818 --> 31:07.169
yet that somehow never feels
quite good enough.

31:07.213 --> 31:10.085
You know, I stole
this dress to fit in,

31:10.129 --> 31:11.086
which is pathetic.

31:11.130 --> 31:12.609
- I don't know
about that.

31:12.653 --> 31:14.307
- Yeah, not as pathetic
as the fact that Peach

31:14.350 --> 31:15.917
wrote me a check
to keep me afloat,

31:15.961 --> 31:18.877
which I don't want to cash
but now I have to.

31:22.184 --> 31:25.231
- Look, if you're
not one of them,

31:25.274 --> 31:28.016
it's just 'cause stuff didn't
just get handed to you.

31:28.060 --> 31:29.583
- It didn't.

31:29.626 --> 31:31.193
- Right, and when
it's like that,

31:31.237 --> 31:35.545
sometimes,
to survive...

31:35.589 --> 31:40.246
you have to show
some teeth.

31:40.289 --> 31:44.467
And I'm guessing that
yours are pretty sharp.

31:51.692 --> 31:54.303
- [groans]

31:54.347 --> 31:56.958
I'm glad we met,
glad we're friends.

31:57.002 --> 31:59.918
- For the love of Christ.

32:05.227 --> 32:07.795
- Joe?
- I know that voice.

32:07.838 --> 32:10.189
- Joe Goldberg?

32:10.232 --> 32:12.931
Maddie Johnson.
I'm Candace's friend.

32:12.974 --> 32:15.237
- Great, a little soon
for you to hear this, Beck,

32:15.281 --> 32:16.456
but here we go.

32:16.499 --> 32:18.806
Wow, Maddie,
that's crazy.

32:18.849 --> 32:20.155
It's so good
to see you.

32:20.199 --> 32:21.548
This is Beck.

32:21.591 --> 32:23.985
- Hey.

32:24.029 --> 32:26.988
So I heard about
you and Candace.

32:27.032 --> 32:29.121
- You know, I thought
we were pretty happy,

32:29.164 --> 32:32.646
but she thought she could be
happier with some guy in Rome.

32:32.689 --> 32:35.475
So you know, I get it.
She's following her bliss.

32:35.518 --> 32:38.695
- It's just how she left
so suddenly.

32:40.828 --> 32:42.221
I mean, we were all
kind of hurt.

32:42.264 --> 32:45.224
- Would you excuse us?
My Uber is here.

32:45.267 --> 32:46.355
It was nice
to meet you.

32:46.399 --> 32:49.663
- Sorry. It was good
to see you, Maddie.

32:52.492 --> 32:56.104
- I just felt like that
needed to be over.

32:56.148 --> 32:59.325
- Let's get you home.

33:04.286 --> 33:05.679
- Be here for Paco.

33:05.722 --> 33:08.508
- What could he possibly
need from me?

33:08.551 --> 33:11.032
- He needs someone who isn't
drunk, Ron, how about that?

33:11.076 --> 33:12.773
[loud thud]

33:14.905 --> 33:18.257
What the hell is wrong
with you, punching a wall?

33:18.300 --> 33:21.042
[indistinct]
solve our problems.

33:21.086 --> 33:23.479
- I'm sorry.

33:23.523 --> 33:24.480
- It's okay.

33:24.524 --> 33:26.178
- It's not okay
to yell.

33:26.221 --> 33:28.049
- Grown-ups do it
all the time.

33:28.093 --> 33:29.137
- Grown-ups
are assholes.

33:29.181 --> 33:31.096
[arguing continues]

33:31.139 --> 33:34.447
Some people used to
yell at me, too, you know.

33:35.709 --> 33:39.060
And I don't want to
be like them.

33:39.104 --> 33:40.192
I got you something.

33:40.235 --> 33:43.195
[somber music]

33:43.238 --> 33:50.245
♪

33:51.638 --> 33:55.642
- I can't take this
in the house.

33:55.685 --> 33:56.643
Ron.

33:56.686 --> 34:00.560
♪

34:00.603 --> 34:02.301
- So all the bathrooms
in the building

34:02.344 --> 34:03.824
have the same kind
of ceiling.

34:03.867 --> 34:05.695
So go in the bathroom.

34:05.739 --> 34:09.830
The ceiling tiles around
the vent move if you push them.

34:09.873 --> 34:11.919
So you push one...
[clicks tongue]

34:11.962 --> 34:16.358
pop the book in there,
slide it closed.

34:16.402 --> 34:18.882
- Like a secret
hiding place.

34:18.926 --> 34:21.059
Cool.

34:21.102 --> 34:22.799
Thank you.

34:22.843 --> 34:25.106
- Mm-hmm.

34:25.150 --> 34:27.891
Have a good night, Paco.

34:30.372 --> 34:33.245
If you want it,
it's here.

34:33.288 --> 34:40.295
♪

34:46.693 --> 34:49.478
You are not responsible
for my feelings,

34:49.522 --> 34:52.133
I am,
but for the record,

34:52.177 --> 34:56.659
I feel like congealed, day-old
egg rolls right about now.

34:56.703 --> 35:00.010
What was the point of
taking me to that party?

35:00.054 --> 35:01.838
Benji was right.

35:01.882 --> 35:03.188
Benji!

35:03.231 --> 35:06.191
[dramatic music]

35:06.234 --> 35:13.198
♪

35:13.241 --> 35:16.549
- [yelling]

35:23.077 --> 35:25.166
- Honestly,
I get how he feels.

35:25.210 --> 35:27.168
- You left me here
to die!

35:27.212 --> 35:29.127
You left me here
to die!

35:29.170 --> 35:32.347
[cries]

35:32.391 --> 35:35.698
Enough of this,
just kill me!

35:48.450 --> 35:51.453
- Hi.
[clears throat]

35:51.497 --> 35:53.803
I--

35:53.847 --> 35:57.416
I just--I want to ask you
to please reconsider.

35:57.459 --> 36:01.071
I need the T.A. job.

36:01.115 --> 36:03.335
I need housing.

36:03.378 --> 36:07.382
Can we maybe discuss placing
me with another adviser?

36:08.514 --> 36:10.342
- It's the middle
of the term.

36:10.385 --> 36:13.127
- I know.

36:13.171 --> 36:15.477
Inconvenient, but it's--

36:15.521 --> 36:18.263
it's really important.

36:18.306 --> 36:20.656
- I wish you the best.

36:20.700 --> 36:24.269
But I really can't,
in good conscience, do that.

36:24.312 --> 36:27.228
- I understand.

36:40.023 --> 36:41.808
So I--

36:41.851 --> 36:44.898
I guess I'm realizing
I have no choice...

36:44.941 --> 36:47.944
[dramatic music]

36:47.988 --> 36:52.514
♪

36:52.558 --> 36:55.300
but to share this.

36:58.041 --> 37:00.305
- And that is?

37:00.348 --> 37:03.482
- Well, it can fit
in one tweet.

37:03.525 --> 37:06.311
A list of six women who
have a story about you.

37:06.354 --> 37:09.052
Not hard to find,
didn't take much asking around.

37:09.096 --> 37:10.184
What's the term again,

37:10.228 --> 37:12.273
harassment or misconduct?

37:12.317 --> 37:14.101
Anyway, they were too scared
to come forward,

37:14.144 --> 37:17.931
but then we realized it's
harder to dismiss seven women

37:17.974 --> 37:19.715
with the same story.

37:19.759 --> 37:22.588
- That's not possible.

37:22.631 --> 37:24.111
I've done nothing
inappropriate.

37:24.154 --> 37:26.461
You want to make yourself
a public liar?

37:26.505 --> 37:29.116
That actually would
sink your career.

37:29.159 --> 37:32.206
Blackmail is not something
you live down.

37:32.250 --> 37:35.383
♪

37:35.427 --> 37:36.645
- You're trying
to call my bluff,

37:36.689 --> 37:39.300
but I'm not bluffing.

37:39.344 --> 37:42.129
So your call.

37:42.172 --> 37:48.527
♪

37:48.570 --> 37:51.312
- I've had a lot of time
to think in here.

37:51.356 --> 37:54.446
You're right.

37:54.489 --> 37:58.624
I am a fraud.

37:58.667 --> 38:03.324
I've done things
worse than you.

38:03.368 --> 38:06.327
And that's how
I know, Joe,

38:06.371 --> 38:08.068
you're not a killer.

38:08.111 --> 38:11.071
[dramatic music]

38:11.114 --> 38:12.507
♪

38:12.551 --> 38:16.119
I want to
tell you something.

38:16.163 --> 38:18.339
And once I tell you,

38:18.383 --> 38:20.341
I'll know
your worst secret.

38:20.385 --> 38:23.562
You'll know mine.

38:23.605 --> 38:27.174
Then you can
let me go.

38:27.217 --> 38:29.785
♪

38:33.746 --> 38:35.574
- [laughs]
[indistinct chatter]

38:35.617 --> 38:37.489
Yeah! We thought
this group was strong.

38:37.532 --> 38:40.535
- A lot of interesting stuff
in Benji's nightstand.

38:40.579 --> 38:42.189
But he was right.

38:42.232 --> 38:45.235
The thumb drive is by far
the most interesting.

38:45.279 --> 38:48.151
It started out your standard
issue frat hazing,

38:48.195 --> 38:51.590
but a certain intensity
kicked in.

38:51.633 --> 38:52.939
- [laughter]

38:52.982 --> 38:55.376
- Then the coke
or the homophobia.

38:55.420 --> 38:56.725
- Teach this bitch a lesson.

38:56.769 --> 38:58.248
Teach him a lesson!

38:58.292 --> 38:59.424
- They all stood there,

38:59.467 --> 39:01.556
laughing.

39:01.600 --> 39:03.384
And Benji...
- Whoo!

39:03.428 --> 39:05.430
- ...was the worst
because he stood there

39:05.473 --> 39:06.909
holding the camera.

39:06.953 --> 39:08.868
- Dumbass,
wake up, dumbass!

39:08.911 --> 39:10.565
[laughs]

39:10.609 --> 39:12.524
Oh, shit!

39:12.567 --> 39:14.134
- Their parents
made it go away,

39:14.177 --> 39:17.093
but Benji kept
a copy of the video,

39:17.137 --> 39:18.878
I assume, to hold over
friends' heads.

39:18.921 --> 39:21.794
Instead, I get to hold it
over Benji's.

39:21.837 --> 39:23.448
And he doesn't
deserve it,

39:23.491 --> 39:25.624
but he's right.

39:25.667 --> 39:28.627
It is enough
to buy his freedom.

39:28.670 --> 39:32.544
[dramatic music]

39:38.376 --> 39:40.552
Should I have changed
the subject on that balcony,

39:40.595 --> 39:42.423
tried to kiss you sooner?

39:42.467 --> 39:44.991
It's not fair how easy it is
to kill a spark.

39:45.034 --> 39:47.297
It's a miracle
love ever happens.

39:47.341 --> 39:48.429
If it's not a myth.

39:48.473 --> 39:50.388
- Hi.

39:50.431 --> 39:54.609
Thanks to you, I showed
that professor some teeth.

39:56.568 --> 39:59.092
- And?

40:00.920 --> 40:01.660
What's that?

40:01.703 --> 40:04.271
- A thank-you doughnut.

40:04.314 --> 40:05.533
It worked.

40:05.577 --> 40:07.666
- Hmm.

40:07.709 --> 40:09.624
That's good. I'm glad.
I mean, I was worried.

40:09.668 --> 40:11.670
- You were right
and I have housing

40:11.713 --> 40:12.801
and can rip
Peach's check up

40:12.845 --> 40:16.544
and generally live
to fight another day.

40:16.588 --> 40:19.460
And I wouldn't have
had the guts if you hadn't--

40:19.504 --> 40:21.375
so really, thank you.

40:21.419 --> 40:23.899
- All I want to do
is help, Beck.

40:23.943 --> 40:26.728
- I mean, you
saw something in me

40:26.772 --> 40:29.601
and, God, not everyone
gets why I'm here

40:29.644 --> 40:31.385
and what being
a writer means.

40:31.429 --> 40:33.474
It's the most--I mean, it's
the only important thing.

40:33.518 --> 40:38.784
And--and you helped me
to not lose it.

40:41.090 --> 40:44.833
Aren't you gonna look, see if
I guessed the right flavor?

40:49.098 --> 40:52.014
No bullshit, classic,
even old-school,

40:52.058 --> 40:53.538
and secretly better than
all those crazy,

40:53.581 --> 40:55.888
trying-too-hard ones.

40:57.933 --> 41:00.849
- It is nice to be seen.

41:00.893 --> 41:02.503
It's a good guess.

41:02.547 --> 41:04.374
- [giggles]

41:06.333 --> 41:07.769
- It's good.

41:07.813 --> 41:10.772
[romantic music]

41:10.816 --> 41:17.823
♪

41:20.565 --> 41:22.218
Come back here.

41:22.262 --> 41:29.225
♪

41:34.796 --> 41:38.583
- So plain glazed, yes.

41:38.626 --> 41:41.063
Noted.

41:42.674 --> 41:44.545
I have to go to class.

41:44.589 --> 41:46.721
- Have a good class,
Beck.

41:46.765 --> 41:49.637
- [laughs]

41:49.681 --> 41:52.640
[somber music]

41:52.684 --> 41:59.691
♪

42:09.657 --> 42:12.051
- Did you get it?
The video?

42:13.748 --> 42:15.663
- Maple latte,
almond milk,

42:15.707 --> 42:18.971
two stevia,
did I get that right?

42:19.014 --> 42:22.583
Yeah, yeah,
I saw the video.

42:22.627 --> 42:25.586
- Yes! Yes!

42:25.630 --> 42:26.718
Yes!

42:26.761 --> 42:29.808
[laughs]

42:29.851 --> 42:33.768
Oh, mutually assured
destruction.

42:33.812 --> 42:35.814
- Let's talk about something
first, though.

42:35.857 --> 42:37.772
What you said
about Beck

42:37.816 --> 42:40.470
basically being
a gold digger...

42:40.514 --> 42:43.648
- I was just being honest,
that's--that's all.

42:43.691 --> 42:44.910
- What you are is wrong.

42:44.953 --> 42:46.912
I'd go so far as to say

42:46.955 --> 42:49.784
you create the problem

42:49.828 --> 42:51.830
when you assume
this stuff,

42:51.873 --> 42:54.789
when you treat her
like trash.

42:54.833 --> 42:58.184
You cast her in a role

42:58.227 --> 43:00.926
that isn't her and--
and you trap her in it.

43:00.969 --> 43:03.929
- Bro, I'm--I'm--
I'm done with her.

43:03.972 --> 43:07.541
- Say I can trust you.

43:07.585 --> 43:08.760
I've got the video, right?

43:08.803 --> 43:12.024
I mean, solid maybe.

43:12.067 --> 43:14.679
The thing is that doesn't make
up for the damage you've done.

43:14.722 --> 43:15.767
- I'm sorry.

43:15.810 --> 43:17.116
- If it was between
me and you, Benji,

43:17.159 --> 43:19.422
honestly, I would
roll the dice.

43:19.466 --> 43:20.815
I would.

43:20.859 --> 43:22.948
Like you said,
I'm not a killer.

43:22.991 --> 43:25.515
[suspenseful music]

43:25.559 --> 43:28.693
But this...

43:28.736 --> 43:29.955
is about her.

43:29.998 --> 43:32.261
- I'm telling...you--

43:32.305 --> 43:33.306
[gulps]

43:33.349 --> 43:34.699
- I'm scared.

43:34.742 --> 43:37.397
I'm very scared of what
you would do to her.

43:37.440 --> 43:40.052
♪

43:40.095 --> 43:40.792
- [gasps]

43:40.835 --> 43:42.576
- Maple almond latte.

43:42.620 --> 43:43.795
- [gasps]

43:43.838 --> 43:45.318
♪

43:45.361 --> 43:47.059
- Two stevia,

43:47.102 --> 43:49.714
two tablespoons
of peanut oil.

43:49.757 --> 43:53.979
♪

43:54.022 --> 43:55.676
Could have gone
either way.

43:55.720 --> 43:57.809
He's lied about
so many things.

43:57.852 --> 44:00.812
Who knew the peanut allergy
was real?

44:00.855 --> 44:07.862
♪

44:14.521 --> 44:17.872
Guess Benji's gonna die
an honest man.

44:17.916 --> 44:24.923
♪
